column14: Even in death, they have their uses. They just need a little encouragement.
To me, brave companions! Feel my radiance flow through you!
Light and unadorned, like wind on water, you will be.
Why should I dodge blows that I do not fear?
Great tacticians learn that consistency often trumps potential.
Stand your ground, child, keep your senses.\r\nThe pain is fleeting, but victory is forever.
Give up everything in pursuit of greatness - even life itself.
What need have I for defence when my enemies\r\nare reduced to ash and splinters?
Lay open your veins, and draw power from your own spilled life.
I give you everything, my pets. My trust, my strength, my safety. Do not disappoint me.
Embrace the pain, drink it in.\r\nYour enemies will know your agony tenfold.
Balance is good in all things, but especially in the realm of magic.
Legend tells of bows so powerful that only giants could draw them back.
Look your foe in the eyes before you pierce him. Delight in his fear.
Let the whistling of arrows and stones be your music.
With enough practice, you can feel the spells\r\ncoming before they're even cast.

column14: The landscape twists before your eyes, morphing into realms of unspeakable horror.
The waters of life roil and flow,\r\nbirthing horrors of flesh and marrow.
Atlassian aberrations engage in a deadly dance.\r\nWill you be joining them in the fray?
In a realm where thought is given form, action and will become one and the same.
You fancy yourself a god. You see only what you want to see.
Embrace the journey, Nomad, for there is no destination.\r\nThis is the prime inescapable truth of eternity.
Ignore everything but your obsession, Nomad.\r\nA mortal life is too short a season to entertain distractions.
A single act of love and defiance may cascade destruction across the cosmos.
You must rise from mere amusement to respected equal.
When memories become twisted by a corrupted mind, history is rewritten, time after time.
Agony born of ennui. Hate born of love.
Constellations are systematically incinerated in the wake of an ever-expanding archive of minds.
At the core of the mass, a fierce hunger seethes, as the Tangle's champion devours a myriad of worlds...
It takes either immense courage or unfettered masochism\r\nto invoke unspeakable horrors, time after time...
You had her curiosity. Now you have her attention.
You were drunk on the power of the cosmos,\r\nuntil a hideous gaze settled upon you,\r\nand tendrils began to unfurl...
A fiery dawn illumines the horizon, and it becomes apparent that all that glitters is not gold...
In lieu of happiness, sometimes the absence of pain is good enough.
Darkening mists shroud the pale sky,\r\nblurring the barrier between nightmare and dream.
The hunter must become the hunted.
The weight of history hangs heavy on the neck of civilisation.
Verisium is often found in a recent crater. Properly refined, it can easily make another.
A good sword is worthless without a hundred plowshares behind it.
Haste is irrelevant in the face of eternity.
What if it's all just in your head?
Do not doubt. Do not question.\r\nThis is the way it has always been.\r\nThis is the way it shall always be.
They are unforgivable sinners and fools...\r\nWe pray each Sacrato. They pray each Kaso.\r\nThey are absolutely mad!
You fight on, muscles burning, limbs leaden,\r\nhoping for that singular moment of victory that\r\nmight finally bring relief... but it never comes.
For nine hundred years, they have had no voice, no hope.\r\nFinally, they have found a kindred soul... in you.
She'll certainly never give you credit now.
The enemy is at the gates. Every single soldier we have may still not be enough...
Within every treasure can be found shades of gold, should one have the patience to look.
Shattered fragments of reality float through the void,\r\nwaiting to be shaped by your mind's desire.
She makes the rules up as she goes.\r\nIt was never going to be fair.
The most enigmatic threshold is not a 'where.'
\"Supplying the Map Device with more power has... unexpected effects.\r\nSomehow, though, I doubt you'll be deterred.\"
Fortune will rain upon those who bring humour to Chaos.
Life and Death are two sides of the same coin.
Life and Death are two sides of the same coin.
Thought cannot exist without Memory.
Memory cannot exist without Thought.
The curious gaze up at the stars...
... and the stars gaze back with hunger.
